  "text": "Others have explored various types of specialized processors for use in a database context (popular examples are GPUTeraSort [CITATION_1] or stream joins for the Cell processor [CITATION_2] ) and they show promising performance characteristics. Given that specialized processors follow an architecture that is not inherently different to the one used in general-purpose CPUs, it is unclear, however, whether they can indeed overcome the limitations of commodity setups.",
